translated: Bollebygd, Älvsborgs län. Born 1st, son of vicar Carl Ninus B. and Anna Mathilda Kylberg. Married in 1927 to Kerstin Bratt. Children: Clara b. 1928, Olof b. 1932, Maia b. 1934, Lena Birgitta b. 1941. Completed high school in Gothenburg in 1911. Graduated with a Bachelor of Medicine from Lund University in 1924 and received a medical license there in 1931. Served as a junior physician in Ramlösa from 1925-1927, acting physician at Tyringe Sanatorium in 1927, acting junior physician at Lund hospital's medical department in 1928 as well as 1931 and 1933, acting district physician in Malmö in 1931, assistant physician at Ahngsås hospital in 1932, acting junior physician for four months, acting provisional physician in Alingsås, Sollebrunn, and Horred districts for a short time from 1933-1934, assistant at the eye clinic in Lund and Kristianstad hospital's ear department in 1934, practicing physician in Gothenburg since 1934, acting district physician there for periods from 1935-1938, and physician for Gothenburg's primary schools from 1936. Hobbies: playing the lute, shooting, and gardening.
